content: At a tech meetup, someone asked if AI could ever be truly ethical. My answer: If we're ethical, why can't our creations be?
Woke up with an idea for a podcast. "AI Ethics: Navigating the Future of Finance." If I'm tweeting about it, might as well record it.
Had a long talk with my colleague about AI and morality. We concluded that AI might just reflect our own ethical inconsistencies.
Just turned 23.2. Reflecting on how my work now feels like shaping the future, not just predicting it. Small steps, big impact.
